-- Veolia Environmental Names New Chief of North America Subsidiary
-- B y   N a d i n e   S k o c z y l a s
-- 2012-12-03T13:21:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-03/veolia-environmental-names-new-chief-of-north-america-subsidiary.html
Veolia Environmental Services North
America, a Chicago-based unit of the French water company  Veolia
Environnement SA (VIE) , named Jeff Adix as chief executive.  Adix replaces Richard Burke, who left to become president
of Advanced Disposal Services, which acquired the assets of
Veolia ES Solid Waste, the company said. Veolia Environmental
Services helps treat, recycle and dispose of hazardous and
industrial waste across North America.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nadine Skoczylas in Jerusalem at 
 nelsibai@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Randall Hackley at 
 rhackley@bloomberg.net  